00:24:18.319 --> 00:24:22.319
And I should say one of the things that I didn't say

00:24:22.319 --> 00:24:24.880
about MCP REPL that is really important

00:24:24.880 --> 00:24:27.839
is that it runs all of your code in a sandbox.

00:24:27.839 --> 00:24:32.800
And so inside that sandbox, it can't connect

00:24:32.800 --> 00:24:34.239
to anything over the network.

00:24:34.239 --> 00:24:36.000
And it can't look at any files

00:24:36.000 --> 00:24:38.239
outside of the current working directory.

00:24:38.239 --> 00:24:40.880
So that's one of the advantages of MCP REPL

00:24:40.880 --> 00:24:43.439
is it allows you to run arbitrary RLM

00:24:43.439 --> 00:24:47.439
and arbitrary R code in a way that's pretty safe.

00:24:47.439 --> 00:24:50.800
And it's using this operating system level sandboxes.

00:24:50.800 --> 00:24:54.239
So there's no way for bad R code to get out

00:24:54.239 --> 00:24:56.000
and do naughty things.

00:24:56.000 --> 00:24:59.920
So this gives you, typically, an LLM

00:24:59.920 --> 00:25:03.680
is not just going to randomly generate really malicious code.

00:25:03.680 --> 00:25:07.359
But this just gives you this nice layer of protection,

00:25:07.359 --> 00:25:09.439
ensuring that it can't do anything

00:25:09.439 --> 00:25:11.520
outside of the directory you're actively working in.

00:25:13.439 --> 00:25:16.000
Awesome.

